<h3>What LG dryer problems do you commonly fix?</h3>
<p>We handle everything from simple belt replacements to complex control board failures. The most common issues our technicians see are blown thermal fuses, faulty heating elements, worn drum belts, and clogged lint systems. LG ThinQ models often need door latch repairs, while older DLGX series units frequently develop motor bearing problems. We also fix error code issues and replace damaged drum seals regularly.</p>
<h3>Do you provide warranties on LG dryer repairs?</h3>
<p>Absolutely. All genuine LG parts come with manufacturer warranties ranging from 90 days to one year depending on the component. We also back our labor with a 90-day service guarantee covering the specific repair we performed. This means if the same problem recurs within 90 days, we'll return and fix it at no additional charge — parts and labor included.</p>
